<quiz>
  <metadata>
    <title>Chapter 1: Rational Numbers</title>
    <class>8</class>
    <subject>Mathematics</subject>
    <chapter>1</chapter>
    <author>G.S. Tutorial</author>
    <timeLimit>25</timeLimit>
    <difficulty>Medium</difficulty>
    <version>1.0</version>
    <lastUpdated>2024-01-15</lastUpdated>
  </metadata>
  
  <question>
    <text>A number that can be expressed in the form p/q where p and q are integers and q ≠ 0 is called:</text>
    <option correct="true">Rational number</option>
    <option correct="false">Irrational number</option>
    <option correct="false">Whole number</option>
    <option correct="false">Natural number</option>
    <explanation>A rational number is any number that can be expressed as a fraction p/q where p and q are integers and q is not zero.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>The additive inverse of 3/5 is:</text>
    <option correct="true">-3/5</option>
    <option correct="false">5/3</option>
    <option correct="false">-5/3</option>
    <option correct="false">3/5</option>
    <explanation>The additive inverse of a number is the number that when added to it gives zero. For 3/5, it's -3/5.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>Which property is illustrated: a × (b + c) = a × b + a × c?</text>
    <option correct="false">Commutative</option>
    <option correct="true">Distributive</option>
    <option correct="false">Associative</option>
    <option correct="false">Closure</option>
    <explanation>This is the distributive property of multiplication over addition.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>The reciprocal of -5/7 is:</text>
    <option correct="false">5/7</option>
    <option correct="true">-7/5</option>
    <option correct="false">7/5</option>
    <option correct="false">-5/7</option>
    <explanation>The reciprocal of a/b is b/a, keeping the sign same. So reciprocal of -5/7 is -7/5.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>Which rational number lies between 1/2 and 3/4?</text>
    <option correct="false">1/4</option>
    <option correct="true">5/8</option>
    <option correct="false">7/8</option>
    <option correct="false">1</option>
    <explanation>5/8 = 0.625 lies between 0.5 (1/2) and 0.75 (3/4).</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>The sum of 2/3 and 4/5 is:</text>
    <option correct="false">6/8</option>
    <option correct="false">8/15</option>
    <option correct="true">22/15</option>
    <option correct="false">6/15</option>
    <explanation>2/3 + 4/5 = (10 + 12)/15 = 22/15.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>Which of these is not a rational number?</text>
    <option correct="false">0</option>
    <option correct="false">-5</option>
    <option correct="true">√2</option>
    <option correct="false">3/4</option>
    <explanation>√2 is an irrational number because it cannot be expressed as a fraction p/q where p and q are integers.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>The product of 2/3 and its reciprocal is:</text>
    <option correct="true">1</option>
    <option correct="false">0</option>
    <option correct="false">4/9</option>
    <option correct="false">9/4</option>
    <explanation>The product of any number and its reciprocal is always 1.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>Which property is illustrated: a + b = b + a?</text>
    <option correct="true">Commutative property of addition</option>
    <option correct="false">Associative property of addition</option>
    <option correct="false">Distributive property</option>
    <option correct="false">Closure property</option>
    <explanation>This is the commutative property of addition, which states that changing the order of addends does not change the sum.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>The multiplicative identity for rational numbers is:</text>
    <option correct="true">1</option>
    <option correct="false">0</option>
    <option correct="false">-1</option>
    <option correct="false">The number itself</option>
    <explanation>1 is the multiplicative identity because any number multiplied by 1 remains unchanged.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>Which is greater: -3/4 or -5/6?</text>
    <option correct="true">-3/4</option>
    <option correct="false">-5/6</option>
    <option correct="false">Both are equal</option>
    <option correct="false">Cannot compare</option>
    <explanation>-3/4 = -0.75 and -5/6 ≈ -0.833. Since -0.75 > -0.833, -3/4 is greater.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>The rational number equivalent to 0.75 is:</text>
    <option correct="false">1/4</option>
    <option correct="false">2/3</option>
    <option correct="true">3/4</option>
    <option correct="false">4/5</option>
    <explanation>0.75 = 75/100 = 3/4 after simplification.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>(-5/8) + (3/8) = ?</text>
    <option correct="false">8/8</option>
    <option correct="true">-2/8</option>
    <option correct="false">2/8</option>
    <option correct="false">-8/8</option>
    <explanation>(-5/8) + (3/8) = (-5 + 3)/8 = -2/8 = -1/4.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>Which of these numbers is between -1 and 0?</text>
    <option correct="false">1/2</option>
    <option correct="true">-1/2</option>
    <option correct="false">2</option>
    <option correct="false">-2</option>
    <explanation>-1/2 = -0.5 lies between -1 and 0.</explanation>
  </question>
  
  <question>
    <text>The standard form of 12/-18 is:</text>
    <option correct="false">12/18</option>
    <option correct="true">-2/3</option>
    <option correct="false">2/3</option>
    <option correct="false">-12/18</option>
    <explanation>12/-18 = -12/18 = -2/3 after simplification.</explanation>
  </question>
</quiz>
